5. Stability Protocols

Signal Conservation Rule

Visibility ∝ Utility × Reuse × Integrity

Prevents hype-driven artifacts.

⸻

Reversibility Gate

No irreversible artifact becomes canonical.

All artifacts must support rollback.

⸻

Translation Invariant

Artifacts must survive translation across two representations.

Example:

concept → code
concept → workflow
concept → diagram


⸻

Attention Budget Constraint

Attention remains limited.

Badger enforces rate limits to prevent overload.

⸻

Kintsugi Feedback Loop

Failures produce improvements.

artifact fails
↓
constraint violation found
↓
repair documented
↓
artifact strengthened


